headline: JPMorgan, Goldman Sachs' new highs: A 'good sign' for the economy
summary: Nvidia's (NVDA) record run isn't the only big move on Wall Street this week: JPMorgan Chase (JPM) and Goldman Sachs (GS) have also hit all-time highs. Truist co-chief investment officer and chief market strategist Keith Lerner, Yahoo Finance Senior Business Reporter Ines Ferré, and Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Allie Canal join Opening Bid host Brian Sozzi to break down what's behind the surge in bank stocks and how investors should approach the sector. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Opening Bid here.

headline: Here’s what Wall Street is saying about Nike ahead of Q4 earnings
summary: Nike (NKE) is expected to report results on its fiscal fourth quarter on Thursday, June 26, with a conference call scheduled for 5:00 pm EDT. What to watch for: GUIDANCE: In March, Nike forecast fourth quarter revenue down in the low- to mid-teens, with gross margin down 400-500 basis points.
